 With spring upon us, it will be fine and cool for most of South Africa on Monday, says the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region: It will be fine and cool in Gauteng but warm in the north. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high. Mpumalanga will experience morning fog patches on the escarpment, otherwise it will be fine and cool but warm in the Lowveld, where it will be partly cloudy. Morning fog patches can be expected on the Limpopo escarpment, otherwise it will be fine and cool but warm in the Lowveld, where it will be partly cloudy. It will be fine and warm in the North West as well as in the Free State but cool in the east. The Northern Cape can expect frost over the southern interior, otherwise it will be fine and warm but cool over the southern parts. The wind along the coast will be fresh to strong south-easterly. In the Western Cape it will be cloudy over the south-west and southern parts with fog patches over the northern parts of the west coast at first, otherwise it will be fine and cool but warm along the west coast. It will remain partly cloudy over the eastern parts of the south coast. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh westerly to south-westerly at first, becoming southerly to south-easterly from the afternoon. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high The Eastern Cape will see morning fog patches over the southern interior, otherwise fine and cool. The wind along the coast will be fresh to strong south westerly, becoming moderate in the evening. Morning fog patches in places in the south are also expected, otherwise it will be fine and cool but partly cloudy along the coast. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh south-westerly. It will be fine and warm in Kwazulu-Natal but cool in the extreme south-west, becoming partly cloudy along the coast and adjacent interior, spreading into the interior in the afternoon. The wind along the coast will be moderate northerly to north-easterly north of Richard's Bay, otherwise southerly to south-westerly. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate. The temperature in your city:         GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter     